               <p>First London Jury, before Mr. Recorder.</p>
               <p>79. 
               
                  <persName id="t18311201-79-defend733" type="defendantName">
                     JOHN 
                     HARRISON
                  <interp inst="t18311201-79-defend733" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-defend733" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-defend733" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-defend733" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18311201-79-off432" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-off432" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-off432" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18311201-79-cd433" type="crimeDate">25th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-79-off432 t18311201-79-cd433"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 3s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18311201-79-victim734" type="victimName">
                        Thomas 
                        Shackleton
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-victim734" type="surname" value="Shackleton"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-79-victim734" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-79-victim734" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-79-off432 t18311201-79-victim734"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-79-person735">
                  THOMAS 
                  SHACKLETON
               <interp inst="t18311201-79-person735" type="surname" value="SHACKLETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person735" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person735" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Goswell-road. On the 25th of November, between eleven and twelve o'clock in the day, I was at the corner of <placeName id="t18311201-79-crimeloc434">Long-lane, Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-79-crimeloc434" type="placeName" value="Long-lane, Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-79-crimeloc434" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-79-off432 t18311201-79-crimeloc434"></join>, coming from St. John-street - there was a cry of Thieves! and people were running - I put my hand into my pocket and my handkerchief was gone; I am sure it was safe half an hour before, when I left home - it was produced to me after the prisoner was secured; I had not seen him near me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-79-person736">
                  JOHN 
                  ROSE
               <interp inst="t18311201-79-person736" type="surname" value="ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person736" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person736" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prisoner near Mr. Shackleton, and saw him take the handkerchief out of Mr. Shackleton's pocket; he had two companious with him - he ran away; I went after him, and lost the other two - there was a cry of Stop thief! and he was stopped at the corner of the first turning, about thirty yards off; I took the handkerchief out of his hand - he denied having had it; Mr. Shackleton claimed it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it off the ground by a picture-shop, and told the officer so.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-79-person737">
                  JOHN 
                  ROSE
               <interp inst="t18311201-79-person737" type="surname" value="ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person737" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-person737" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18311201-79-verdict435" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-verdict435" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19. - <rs id="t18311201-79-punish436" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-79-punish436" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-79-defend733 t18311201-79-punish436"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
